verbose_text: Subjects with the GG genotype exhibited higher FSH levels (3.37 +/- 1.79 IU/l, n = 423) compared with heterozygotes (2.84 +/- 1.54 IU/l, n = 125) (P = 0.0005), the group of T-allele carriers (GT+ TT, 2.78 +/- 1.51 IU/l, n = 131) (P = 0.0005) and TT-homozygotes (2.02 +/- 0.81 IU/L, n = 6) (P = 0.031).
